The flavors are delicious. I recommend browning the chicken in much less olive oil (around 3T), poured directly from the sundried tomato jar. Deglaze with a drinkable red wine. Then toss in the entirety of the sauce ingredients--you'll probably want to double the liquid components of the sauce. Simmer for longer than called for--at least 20 minutes. Divine!

Rating: 4
My boyfriend just joined a cycling team. He requests that I make him this dish the night before he races. We have renamed it "Power Pasta" in our house. I made some slight adjustments. First, I make a sauce by using less olive oil, just a few tablespoons, and in addition to the balsamic, I throw in some red wine (whatever I'm drinking when I'm cooking this dish is what goes in) - maybe about 1/4 cup or so, and then all of the other ingredients (except chicken). Then, I brown the chicken breast in a large sauted pan. Pour the sauce over, and then I let it reduce around the chicken breast. It comes out so rich and delicious. It's fabulous!

