This recipe is the greatest. I always make the dressing ahead of time, and I can cook it in about 15 minutes flat when my husband gets home. I make this ALL the time. I have made the following modifications, but I think it all depends on your own taste: I use 6 tbsp balsamic vinegar, 1/2 cup red onion, can subs the basil with 3 tbsp pesto (or even do a little of both), 1/4 cup of oil, 1 cup chicken broth, 1/2tsp salt, 1/4 tsp pepper, and increase linguini anywhere from 1 to 1.5lb. Top it with freshly grated parmesan, and you have a winner that can be served during the week or for company.

